  "What is adaptive management in environmental policy?": "",
  "An approach of implementing policies, monitoring outcomes, and adjusting strategies based on what is working and what is not": "",
  "A fixed policy approach that never changes once implemented": "",
  "A system where environmental regulations are automatically renewed every five years": "",
  "A policy that only adapts to economic changes, not environmental outcomes": "",
  "Adaptive management is a structured, iterative approach to policy that treats implementation as an experiment: outcomes are monitored systematically, and policies are adjusted in response to new evidence about what works.": "",
