  "A state wants to reduce mercury emissions from coal-fired power plants. Option A is a command-and-control regulation requiring specific scrubber technology. Option B is a cap-and-trade program setting an overall mercury cap and letting plants trade emission permits. Based on the Acid Rain Program's experience, which approach would likely achieve the environmental goal at lower cost and why?": "",
