  "After a major chemical plant explosion, public outrage leads politicians to propose strict new regulations. Industry lobbyists argue that the regulations will cost billions and cause plant closures. An economic study shows the regulations' health benefits would be worth $30 billion annually while compliance would cost $1 billion. Based on the Clean Air Act's benefit-to-cost experience, how should policymakers evaluate this situation?": "",
